Package models

Class Camp

java.lang.Object
models.Camp
public class Camp extends Object
The Camp class represents a camp in CAMs. Each camp has a unique name, schedule, registration details, description, and staff in charge. It also manages information about attendees, committee members, enquiries, suggestions, and visibility.
Since:
1.0
Version:
1.0
Author:
Chin Jun Hao, Mark

      Constructor used for importing Camp from CSV.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the camp.
      dates - The list of dates on which the camp is scheduled.
      registrationClosingDate - The closing date for camp registration.
      openTo - The faculty to which the camp is open.
      location - The location where the camp is held.
      totalSlots - The total number of available slots for the camp.
      committeeSlots - The number of slots reserved for committee members.
      description - A brief description of the camp.
      staffInCharge - The name of the staff in charge of the camp.
      attendees - A list of names of attendees registered for the camp.
      withdrawnAttendees - A list of names of attendees who have withdrawn from the camp.
      committeeMembers - A list of names of committee members involved in the camp.
      enquiries - A map associating enquiry IDs with their respective enquiries.
      suggestions - A map associating suggestion IDs with their respective suggestions.
      visibility - The visibility status indicating whether the camp is open for registration.
